Subject:    How do I obtain complete DNS software for Suns?
From:       <a href="?a=95837817000029&r=1&w=2">metaphor!xymox.metaphor.com!philf () apple ! com  (Phil Fernandez)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=199004">1990-04-28 23:14:31</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797326965&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797326965&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


I am looking to install a DNS name server and client BIND software
here at Metaphor.  We run a Sun environment with several Sun 3 and
Sparc servers and about 150 workstations, a mixture of Sun 3 and
Sparcstations.  We run SunOS 4.0.3 or 4.1, and currently use YP for
network name service.

I would like to move the bulk of our name lookup services to a DNS
server -- not because I think it's going to be of operational benefit
in our environment, but as a training / experimental platform to learn
some things before designing the name services environment for an
upcomping product.

Is there a freely-distributable DNS server for SunOS4 available
somewhere on the Internet?  Does this distribution include client BIND
software?

I'd also appreciate any thoughts, insights, etc. that you might have
to offer.

I prefer responses by e-mail.

pmf

